HEADWORD: Psaltery
<hw>Psal"ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Psalteries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>sautrie</ets>,
OF. <ets>psalterie</ets>, F. <ets>psalt⟦eacute⟧rion</ets>, L.
<ets>psalterium</ets> psaltery, psalter, from Gr. <?/, fr. <?/. See
<er>Psalm</er>, <er>Psalter</er>.]</ety> <def>A stringed instrument of
music used by the Hebrews, the form of which is not known.</def>⟦br⟧
